{[%mdl 8256] A54: Old Indian Defence with Nf3, but without e4} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3
Nf6 3. Nf3 d6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Nbd7 $146 (5... g6 6. g3 (6. Bg5 Bg7 7. e3 h6
8. Bh4 Nc6 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Be2 Rb8 11. Qc2 O-O 12. O-O Re8 13. Rac1 c5 14. Bf3
Bf5 15. e4 Bd7 16. Bg3 Qc8 17. Rfe1 {1/2-1/2 (17) Kaidanov,G (2605)-Martin Del
Campo C,R (2445) Dallas 1996}) 6... Bg7 (6... Nc6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Bg2 Bd7 9.
Bg5 Bg7 10. Qd2 O-O 11. O-O Re8 12. Rad1 Qc8 13. Rfe1 Bh3 14. Bxc6 Rb8 15. Bxe8
Qxe8 16. b3 Qe5 17. e4 Bg4 18. Rc1 h6 19. Bxh6 Qh5 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. h4 {
Haslinger,S (2410)-Ankerst,M (2362) Dos Hermanas 2004 1-0}) 7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O
Nbd7 (8... a6 9. b3 Re8 10. Bb2 Nbd7 11. Re1 Rb8 12. Qd2 c5 13. Nc2 Nb6 14. e4
Be6 15. Rad1 Bf8 16. h3 Na8 17. Ne3 Nc7 18. Qc2 Qe7 19. f4 Bg7 20. Qf2 b5 21.
f5 Bd7 22. g4 g5 23. Qd2 {Kubien,J (2305)-Dzieniszewski,A (2230) Tarnow 1979
1-0 (41)}) 9. b3 Re8 10. Bb2 c6 11. Rb1 a5 12. e3 Nc5 13. a3 Qb6 14. Ba1 Ng4
15. h3 Nxe3 16. fxe3 Rxe3 17. Kh2 Rd3 18. Qe2 Qd8 19. Ne4 Bxd4 20. Nxc5 {
Christiansen,L (2500)-Henley,R (2340) Lone Pine 1978 1/2-1/2 (50)}) (5... Bd7
6. g3 Nc6 7. Bg2 Qc8 8. h3 Be7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Rc1 Re8 11. a3 Ne5 12. Qb3 Rb8
13. Nd5 Bd8 14. Nb5 Bxb5 15. cxb5 c5 16. O-O Qe6 17. Rfd1 Nxd5 18. Rxd5 Nd7 19.
Qd1 Bc7 20. Rd2 {Vigh,B (2340)-Peisser,M (2250) Hartberg 1991 1-0 (37)}) 6. e4
{Black has a cramped position. Black's piece can't move: c8} Nc5 {Black
threatens to win material: Nc5xe4} 7. Qc2 Nfxe4 $2 (7... a5 $142 $14 {is the
best option Black has}) 8. Nxe4 $18 Qe7 9. Bd3 $4 {weakening the position} (9.
f3 $5 a6 $18) 9... Nxe4 $2 (9... f5 $142 {and Black is still in the game} 10.
Kd1 Nxd3 $11) 10. Bxe4 $16 f5 11. O-O fxe4 (11... Qxe4 $142 $5 12. Qc3 Kf7 $16)
12. Re1 $18 Qf7 $4 {a blunder in a bad position} (12... Kf7 $142 13. Rxe4 Qd8
$18) 13. Qxe4+ Be7 14. Bg5 O-O 15. Bxe7 Qxf2+ 16. Kh1 Re8 (16... Rf7 {hardly
improves anything} 17. Qd5 Bg4 18. Qxb7 $18) 17. Rf1 (17. Qd5+ $142 {makes it
even easier for White} Qf7 18. Nb5 $18) 17... Qxd4 (17... Qxb2 {there is
nothing better in the position} 18. Rab1 Qd2 $18) 18. Qxd4 Rxe7 19. Rf2 (19.
Qh4 $142 $5 {might be the shorter path} Re8 20. Rae1 Be6 $18) 19... Be6 20.
Raf1 Rae8 21. b3 b6 22. h3 h6 (22... a5 {a fruitless try to alter the course
of the game} 23. Re1 $18) 23. a4 a6 24. Qd3 Bf7 25. Rxf7 $1 {Mate threat} (25.
Rxf7 Rxf7 26. Qd5 $18) 1-0

