Qd6 26. Bg3 Bxg5 (26... Bc6 $5 $17) 27. fxg5 $11 {Opposite coloured bishops
appeared} Qe7 28. h4 Kf7 (28... Bc6 29. Qe2 Qe6 30. Qf2 $11) 29. a3 (29. a4 a6
$14) 29... Reh8 $11 30. Rf4 Bd5 {A comfortable square for the black bishop} 31.
Raf1 Rd8 32. Qe2 Kg8 (32... Rhh8 $142 $5 $11 {would keep Black in the game})
33. Rxf5 $1 $16 {Deflection: h5. .} Rxh4 $4 {strolling merrily down the path
