{[%mdl 8192] D07: Queen's Gambit: Chigorin Defence} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e5 3. e3 Nc6
4. Nc3 (4. dxe5 d4 5. a3 dxe3 6. Qxd8+ Kxd8 7. Bxe3 Nxe5 8. Nc3 Be6 9. O-O-O+
Kc8 10. c5 Nf6 11. h3 a5 12. g4 h5 13. f4 Nc6 14. g5 Nd7 15. Ne4 a4 16. Bd3 Ra5
17. Bd2 Rxc5+ 18. Nxc5 Nxc5 {Nikolic,P (2645)-Piket,J (2570) Monte Carlo 1996
0-1 (60)}) 4... Bb4 5. Bd2 $146 (5. Nf3 Bg4 6. Be2 exd4 7. exd4 dxc4 8. d5
Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Bxf3 10. gxf3 Ne5 11. Ba3 Ne7 12. Qd4 Qxd5 13. Bxe7 Qe6 14. O-O-O
Qxe7 15. f4 Ng6 16. Qxg7 f6 17. Qh6 Qa3+ 18. Kb1 Qxc3 19. Bxc4 Qxc4 {Williams,
S (2455)-Rogers,J (2307) England 2013 1-0}) 5... Nf6 6. a3 (6. dxe5 Nxe5 7.
Qa4+ Nc6 $14) 6... Bxc3 $11 7. Bxc3 exd4 8. exd4 {White has the pair of
bishops.} O-O {Black castles and improves king safety} 9. Bd3 Re8+ 10. Ne2 Ne7
11. O-O c6 12. Qc2 Ng6 13. Ng3 (13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. Rfe1 Be6 $11) 13... Nf4 14.
f3 {Prevents intrusion on e4+g4} dxc4 15. Bxc4 b5 16. Bb3 N4d5 {A sound move}
17. Rfe1 Be6 18. Bd2 Rc8 19. Ne4 Nxe4 20. fxe4 Nb6 21. Bxe6 Rxe6 22. Bc3 Nc4
23. Qd3 Ne5 {Black threatens to win material: Ne5xd3} 24. Qe2 Ng6 25. e5 {
White has a new backward pawn: d4} Nf4 {Black threatens to win material: Nf4xe2
} 26. Qg4 $4 {White loses the upper hand} (26. Qf3 Nd5 $11) 26... Nd5 $4 {
throwing away the advantage} (26... Nxg2 $142 {would have given Black a clear
advantage} 27. Re2 Rg6 28. Qxg6 hxg6 29. Rxg2 a5 $19) 27. Qe4 Qg5 28. Bd2 $4 (
28. Rad1 $142 $11 {is just about the only chance}) 28... Qxd2 $19 (28... Qxd2
29. Re2 Qf4 $19) 0-1

