{[%mdl 8192] D48: Semi-Slav: Meran System: 7...b5 8 Bd3 a6} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6
3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 e6 5. Bd3 Nbd7 6. Nc3 dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 a6 9. O-O Be7
$146 (9... c5 10. dxc5 (10. Ne5 Bb7 11. f4 g6 12. b3 cxd4 13. Nxb5 axb5 14.
Bxb5 Bg7 15. a4 O-O 16. Ba3 Nxe5 17. fxe5 Nd5 18. Qf3 Qb6 19. Bxf8 Rxf8 20.
exd4 Bxe5 21. Rad1 Bxd4+ 22. Rxd4 Qxd4+ 23. Kh1 Ba8 24. Be8 Ne3 {Astasio Lopez,
D (2392)-Korneev,O (2625) Linares 2013 0-1}) (10. a3 Bb7 11. Qe2 Qc7 12. e4
cxd4 13. Nxd4 Bc5 14. Nb3 Ba7 15. Bg5 O-O 16. Rac1 Qe5 17. Be3 Bxe3 18. Qxe3
Ng4 19. Qh3 f5 20. exf5 exf5 21. Rfe1 Qf4 22. Qg3 Qxg3 23. hxg3 Nde5 24. Bf1 f4
{Varlan,H (2163)-Dobre,C (2357) Olanesti 2013 0-1 (61)}) (10. Re1 Bb7 11. a3
Be7 12. b3 O-O 13. Bb2 Qb6 14. Bf1 Rfd8 15. Qe2 Rac8 16. Rad1 cxd4 17. Nxd4
Bxa3 18. Bxa3 Rxc3 19. Bb4 Rcc8 20. Qa2 Re8 21. Ba5 Qc5 22. Qa1 Qg5 23. f4 Qg6
24. Qb2 Nc5 {Adam,W (2200)-La Rota,F (2310) New York 1979 0-1 (45)}) 10... Nxc5
11. Be2 (11. Bc2 Bb7 12. a3 Qc7 13. Qe2 Nce4 14. Bd2 Bd6 15. Nxe4 Nxe4 16. Bxe4
Bxe4 17. Bc3 O-O 18. h3 Qb7 19. Rfd1 Rfd8 20. Ng5 Bg6 21. Nf3 a5 22. Rd2 b4 23.
axb4 axb4 24. Rxa8 Qxa8 25. Be5 Be7 {Tolnai,T (2230)-Szabolcsi,J (2245)
Budapest 1982 1/2-1/2 (46)}) 11... Bb7 12. Qxd8+ Rxd8 13. Rd1 Rxd1+ 14. Nxd1
Bd6 15. b3 Nd5 16. Bb2 f6 17. Nc3 Nxc3 18. Bxc3 Ne4 19. Be1 Ba3 20. Nd4 e5 21.
Nc2 Bb2 22. Rb1 Bc3 23. Bf3 Bxe1 24. Nxe1 {Capablanca,J-Bernstein,O Moscow
1914 1/2-1/2}) (9... c5 10. a4 b4 11. Ne4 $11) 10. e4 $14 {Black has a cramped
position} Qc7 (10... O-O 11. e5 Nd5 12. Qc2 $14) 11. e5 $16 Nd5 12. Ne4 {
White has an active position} (12. Nxd5 cxd5 13. Bg5 Nb6 $16) 12... O-O {
White has a very active position} 13. Kh1 (13. Bg5 Bxg5 14. Nexg5 h6 15. Bh7+
Kh8 $14) 13... f6 {Consolidates g5} (13... c5 14. Nxc5 Nxc5 15. dxc5 Qxc5 16.
Bd2 $11) 14. b3 (14. exf6 N7xf6 15. Qe2 Ng4 $14) 14... fxe5 15. Neg5 Bxg5 16.
Nxg5 {White forks: e6+h7} N5f6 $4 {Black lets it slip away} (16... N7f6 $142 {
would save the game} 17. Ba3 b4 $11) 17. Nxe6 $18 Qd6 18. Nxf8 Kxf8 (18... Nxf8
19. dxe5 Qxe5 20. Ba3 $18) 19. Qc2 (19. dxe5 $142 {keeps an even firmer grip}
Nxe5 20. Bc2 Qxd1 21. Rxd1 Nf7 $18) 19... g6 $4 {terrible, but what else could
Black do to save the game?.} (19... exd4 $142 20. Bxh7 c5 $18) 20. dxe5 $18
Nxe5 21. Rd1 (21. Bf4 {might be the shorter path} Bd7 22. Rad1 Nd5 $18) 21...
Nd5 (21... Neg4 22. g3 Be6 23. Bf4 Bd5+ 24. Kg1 $18) 22. Be4 Ng4 23. Bxd5 $4 {
makes life more difficult} (23. g3 $142 {and White can celebrate victory} Ngf6
24. Bxg6 $18) 23... Qxh2# 0-1

