6. O-O Qc7 7. d4 Ne4 8. c3 g5 9. Ne5 Nxe5 10. fxe5 f5 11. Bh5+ Kd8 12. Nd2 e6
13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. g4 Be7 15. gxf5 exf5 16. Bf7 Qb6 17. d5 Qh6 18. d6 Bf8 19.
Qd5 Bc6 {Villalba,H (2220)-Moreda,L (2275) Buenos Aires 1997 1-0}) (5. Bxd7+
Nbxd7 6. b3 g6 7. Bb2 Bg7 8. O-O e6 9. Qe2 O-O 10. d3 b5 11. Nbd2 Qb6 12. Kh1
Rac8 13. Rab1 Qc7 14. c4 bxc4 15. dxc4 Ne8 16. Qd3 Nb6 17. Ne5 Nd6 18. Ng4 f6
19. Rbc1 dxc4 {Tereladze,S (2223)-Gvetadze,S (2313) Batumi 2002 1/2-1/2}) 5...
a6 6. Bxd7+ Nbxd7 7. O-O g6 8. b3 Bg7 9. Bb2 O-O 10. a4 Rc8 11. Na3 e6 12. c4
Qe7 13. a5 Ne8 14. Bxg7 Nxg7 15. Qd3 Nf6 16. Qc3 Rfd8 17. Nc2 Nf5 18. Rae1 d4 (
18... Ne4 19. Qd3 $15) 19. exd4 $11 cxd4 20. Qb4 Qxb4 {Black forks: a5+b3} 21.
Nxb4 Rc5 {Black threatens to win material: Rc5xa5} (21... d3 22. g3 $11) 22.
Re5 {White threatens to win material: Re5xc5} Nd7 {Black threatens to win
material: Nd7xe5} 23. Nd3 {White threatens to win material: Nd3xc5} Rcc8 24.
Re4 Nf6 25. Ree1 h5 26. Ng5 Ne7 27. Rc1 Nc6 28. b4 Kg7 29. Rc2 Nh7 30. Ne4 f5
$2 (30... Nf6 $142 {and Black could well hope to play on} 31. Nxf6 Kxf6 $11)
31. Nec5 $18 Kf7 $4 {shortens the misery for Black} (31... Nf8 $142 32. Nxb7
Nxb4 33. Nxb4 Rd7 $18) 32. Nxb7 Rd7 33. Nbc5 (33. Ndc5 {makes it even easier
for White} Rxb7 34. Nxb7 Ke7 $18) 33... Ra7 (33... Nxb4 {doesn't do any good}
34. Ne5+ Kg7 35. Nxe6+ Kg8 $18) 34. Nb3 (34. b5 $142 $5 {might be the shorter
path} Nxa5 35. b6 Re7 $18) 34... Rb8 $2 (34... Nxb4 $142 35. Nxb4 Rb7 $16) 35.
Ne5+ $4 {ruins a very nice position} (35. Rb1 $142 {and White has prevailed}
Rxb4 36. Nxb4 Nxb4 37. Rcc1 $18) 35... Nxe5 $14 36. fxe5 Rxb4 37. Nxd4 Rc7 {
Black threatens to win material: Rc7xc4} 38. d3 {White has a new protected
passed pawn: c4} Ra4 (38... Nf8 39. Nf3 $14) 39. Nb3 (39. Rb1 $5 Rxa5 40. c5
Raxc5 41. Rxc5 Rxc5 42. Rb7+ Kg8 43. Nxe6 Rxe5 44. Rg7+ Kh8 45. Rxg6 $16) 39...
Rb7 $4 (39... Nf8 $142 $14 {the rescuing straw}) 40. Nc5 $18 (40. Nc5 Rab4 41.
Nxb7 Rxb7 42. c5 $18) 1-0

