16. Nce3 $5 {looks like a viable alternative} fxe4 17. Bxe4 $11) 16... fxe4 $15
17. Bxe4 {White has a king attack} f5 $4 {Black has let it slip away} (17...
Nd4 18. Ncb6 Ra7 19. Rfd1 $15) 18. Nf6+ $4 {gives the opponent counterplay} (
18. Ncb6 $142 $18 {and White gets the upper hand}) 18... Rxf6 (18... Qxf6 $5 {
might be a viable alternative} 19. Bxc6 Rad8 $11) 19. Bxc6 $14 Rc8 {Black
threatens to win material: Rc8xc6} 20. Bb7 $4 {gives the opponent new chances}
(20. Ne3 $142 {saving the game} Bxa2 21. Bd5+ Bxd5 22. Nxd5 $14) 20... Rxc4 $19
21. Rxc4 Bxc4 22. Rc1 d5 23. b3 Qd7 24. bxc4 Qxb7 25. cxd5 (25. Qe8+ {hardly
improves anything} Kh7 26. Qxe5 dxc4 $19) 25... Qxd5 26. h3 (26. a3 {does not
save the day} Rd6 $19) 26... Kh7 27. Qe2 Rg6 {[%cal Ye5e4] Black plans e4} 28.
f3 (28. g3 {is no salvation} e4 29. Kh2 Rd6 $19) 28... e4 29. f4 (29. fxe4 {
is still a small chance} Bd4+ 30. Kh1 Qxe4 31. Rc7+ Rg7 32. Rxg7+ Kxg7 33. Qf1
$19) 29... Bd4+ 30. Kh2 e3 (30... Qd6 $142 {might be the shorter path} 31. Qf1
Be3 $19) 31. g3 (31. Rc7+ {otherwise it's curtains at once} Rg7 32. Rc2 $19)
31... Rc6 32. Rb1 (32. Rxc6 Qxc6 33. a4 Qxa4 34. Kg1 Qa1+ 35. Kg2 a5 36. g4 Qb2
37. Qxb2 Bxb2 38. Kf3 a4 39. gxf5 a3 40. Kxe3 Bf6 41. Kd3 a2 42. h4 a1=Q 43.
Ke3 Qc3+ 44. Ke2 h5 45. Kf2 Qd3 46. Kg1 Qf3 47. Kh2 Qg4 48. Kh1 Qh3+ 49. Kg1
Bd4#) 32... Rb6 (32... Qe4 33. Rb7+ Kg6 34. h4 Rc2 35. h5+ Kf6 36. Qxc2 Qxc2+
37. Kh3 Qe4 38. Kh2 Qxb7 39. a4 Qf3 40. g4 Qxg4 41. a5 e2 42. Kh1 Qg1#) 33. Rc1
Rb2 34. Rc2 Rb1 (34... Qxa2 $1 35. Rxb2 Qxb2 36. Qxb2 Bxb2 37. Kg2 a5 38. Kf3
