3 Bf4} 1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c3 e6 4. Bf4 Be7 (4... Bd6 5. e3 O-O 6. Nbd2 b6
7. Ne5 Nfd7 8. Bd3 Bxe5 9. dxe5 Ba6 10. Bc2 Nc6 11. Nf3 f6 12. exf6 Nxf6 13.
Nd4 Nxd4 14. Qxd4 c5 15. Qe5 Qe8 16. h3 Rc8 17. O-O-O b5 18. Qg5 b4 19. Be5 {
Soppe,G (2471)-Milov,V (2626) Buenos Aires 2000 0-1 (37)}) 5. e3 (5. h3 O-O 6.
e3 b6 7. Nbd2 c5 8. Ne5 Nfd7 9. Nxd7 Qxd7 10. Nf3 Ba6 11. Ne5 Qb7 12. Nd3 Nd7
13. Be2 Rfe8 14. O-O Bf6 15. Re1 Rad8 16. Qa4 Bc4 17. Qc2 h6 18. Red1 a5 19.
Bf3 Qa7 {Mesropov,K (2419)-Makhmutov,R (2315) Moscow 2012 1/2-1/2 (45)}) 5...
O-O 6. Bd3 Nbd7 $146 (6... b6 7. Ne5 Bb7 8. O-O c5 9. Nd2 a6 10. Qf3 Nbd7 11.
Qh3 Re8 12. Ndf3 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 g6 14. g4 Kg7 15. Bh6+ Kg8 16. Qf3 Rf8 17. Bxf8
Qxf8 18. Qg2 Ne4 19. f3 Nd6 20. dxc5 bxc5 21. Nd7 {Tologontegin,S (2335)
-Akkozov,B (2369) Tashkent 2011 1/2-1/2 (51)}) 7. Nbd2 c5 {Black's piece can't
move: c8} 8. O-O b5 (8... Nh5 9. Qc2 h6 10. Be5 $11) 9. Ne5 (9. Bxb5 $5 Qb6 10.
Qa4 $16) 9... Qb6 $11 10. Rc1 Bd6 11. c4 cxd4 12. Qf3 $4 {there were better
ways to keep up the pressure} (12. Nxd7 $142 {this is the best bet to save the
position} Nxd7 13. cxd5 Bxf4 14. exf4 $11) 12... Nxe5 $19 13. Bxe5 Bxe5 14. c5
Qc6 (14... Qb8 {keeps an even firmer grip} 15. g3 dxe3 16. Qxe3 Bxb2 17. Rb1
$19) 15. Nb3 (15. exd4 {does not help much} Bxd4 16. Rc2 e5 $19) 15... a6 (
15... dxe3 $142 {makes sure everything is clear} 16. fxe3 Bxb2 17. Nd4 Bxd4 18.
exd4 $19) 16. exd4 Bc7 17. Rfe1 (17. Qe2 Bb7 $19) 17... Bb7 18. Qh3 Rfe8 19. g3
(19. Qf3 Bc8 $19) 19... e5 20. f4 (20. Qg2 {is not much help} e4 21. Be2 h6 $19
) 20... Bc8 (20... exf4 $142 $5 {seems even better} 21. gxf4 Bxf4 22. Rcd1
Rxe1+ 23. Rxe1 $19) 21. Qh4 (21. f5 {hardly improves anything} exd4 22. Qh4
Rxe1+ 23. Rxe1 Bb7 $19) 21... exf4 22. Rf1 (22. gxf4 {is no salvation} Ne4 $19)
22... h6 (22... Re3 $142 {and Black takes home the point} 23. Rcd1 fxg3 24. h3
$19) 23. gxf4 (23. Rxf4 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} Bxf4 24. Qxf4 Bg4
$19) 23... Bg4 24. Rce1 Rxe1 25. Rxe1 Bxf4 26. h3 Bg5 27. Qg3 Bxh3 (27... Be6
$142 {and Black can already relax} 28. h4 Nh5 29. Qf2 $19) 28. Re5 (28. Qxh3
Re8 29. Kf1 $19) 28... Be6 29. Na5 (29. Qf3 {doesn't improve anything} Re8 $19)
29... Qc7 30. b4 (30. Rxg5 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game}
Qxa5 31. Rxg7+ Kf8 32. Qg2 Qe1+ 33. Bf1 Qe3+ 34. Kh1 Qxd4 35. Rg3 $19) 30...
Nd7 (30... Ng4 $142 {and the rest is a matter of technique} 31. Kg2 Nxe5 32.
Qxe5 Qxe5 33. dxe5 d4 $19) 31. Qf2 $4 {terrible, but the game is lost in any
case} (31. Rxg5 $142 Qxg3+ 32. Rxg3 $17) 31... Nxe5 $19 (31... Nxe5 32. dxe5
Qxe5 $19) 0-1

